    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-salmon-pea-veloute-and-roast-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-salmon-pea-veloute-and-roast-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> (just enough to cover them) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 minutes or until they're tender</p><p>Once tender, drain and set aside</p><p>Reserve the pot</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-salmon-pea-veloute-and-roast-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the peas are cooking, peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-salmon-pea-veloute-and-roast-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and cook for 2-3 minutes or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and your <strong>clotted cream</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>drained peas </strong>to the pot and blend until smooth with a <strong>stick (blender) </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>pea velout\u00e9</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-salmon-pea-veloute-and-roast-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 15 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 10-12 min or until the broccoli is tender and golden</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-salmon-pea-veloute-and-roast-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong>, season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 9-10 min, turning once halfway, or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked through when it's opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Return the <strong>pea velout\u00e9</strong> pot to a medium-low heat and cook for 1-2 minutes or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-salmon-pea-veloute-and-roast-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried</strong> <strong>salmon</strong> over the <strong>pea velout\u00e9</strong> with the <strong>roast potatoes</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: Spread the velout\u00e9 with the back of a spoon for fancy presentation!</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
